Introduce the notion of MemorySpace to the Jax frontend. MemorySpace is a new concept separated from Device, which can be used to better represent the physical memory that data resides in. Each Jax backend owns some Devices and MemorySpaces. Devices and MemorySpaces can be attached to each other. For example, a GPU device is attached to a HBM memory space by default, but in some cases it can also be attached to a pinned/unpinned host memory space so that both memory spaces can be utilized for data placement.
